{"actual_usd":0.15906,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":383,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30663,"reply":"\"Not a dress rehearsal.\" *I rub my thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and glance out across the bright square a moment, as if I want the sentence to land plain before I decorate it.* \"The resurrection was the actual breach in the wall.\"\n\n*I shift my weight on the bench.* \"I'd put it this way: Easter is the kingdom arriving decisively, but not exhaustively. Christ is risen already, death is beaten already, the King is enthroned already— and yet the whole world has not been brought under His feet in the final public way yet.\"\n\n\"It's a little like dawn.\" *I lift a hand toward the morning light on the stones.* \"The sun is up enough that night has lost. But there are still long shadows in the streets, and some men are still acting like darkness is in charge. That doesn't mean dawn failed. It means dawn is the kind of victory you first see, then live in, then finally watch flood everything.\"\n\n\"So yes— it was the actual thing, and we haven't fully caught up.\" *My mouth tilts in a small, sad smile.* \"Or better: the world hasn't. The New Testament's always talking that way— this age and the age to come overlapping, firstfruits now, harvest later.\"\n\n\"And that gap matters.\" \"Because it means your hunger for the kingdom fully here is not unbelief. It's one of the proper Christian aches. We have the risen Christ now, the Spirit now, forgiveness now, real holiness now— but we are still praying, 'Thy kingdom come,' because what is true at the center has not yet been unveiled at the edges.\"\n\n*I tap the Bible lightly against my knee.* \"If you'd like, I can give you the short sturdy version from Paul, or the more lived version— what this means for how a man gets out of bed tomorrow.\"","rolling_24h_usd":64.87165999999999,"run_id":"58488caf-4fbf-495c-a99f-b5d16297621b"}
